name: Justin's Favorite Smokies
author: TXCOOKINGPRINCESS
summary: If you like pigs in a blanket and cocktail weenies - this is the recipe for you!  Barbeque sauce and cheese add a tantalizing twist to the mix.
directions: Preheat an oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Spoon a teaspoon of barbeque sauce in the center of each flattened biscuit
Sprinkle a teaspoon of cheese over barbeque sauce; top with cocktail wiener
Pull opposite sides of each biscuit together to form a taco shape
Press edges together to seal; fold over to one side, pressing biscuit down on itself
Arrange filled biscuits on 2 baking sheets
Bake in preheated oven until golden brown, about 10 minutes
Allow to cool slightly before serving
